SUMMARY:FREE CONCERT  Duck at Lake Raleigh 
DESCRIPTION:Raleigh & Triangle Activities Meetup Group\n**DUCK**\n\n**Thur
 sday\, April 9\, 2026**\n\n*Get your boogie on when Duck takes the stage f
 or our first LIVE at Lake Raleigh concert of the season! This funky\, blue
 sy\, jazzy band brings the party. Like their t-shirts say\, it’s time fo
 r DUCK\, DUCK\, GROOVE. And you’ll be catching them LIVE the night befor
 e their new album (“Funk Prayer”) drops.*\n\n**Parking for LIVE @ Lake
  Raleigh**\nAll of Centennial Campus offers free parking after 5 p.m. Ther
 e’s street and lot parking throughout Centennial. Parking lots and decks
  near the concert.\n\n**Food and Drink**\nBring you own food and drink to 
 enjoy or food trucks will be on site. They’ll be announced on the [Live 
 @ Lake Raleigh website.](https://live.arts.ncsu.edu/livelake-raleigh/)\nIn
  addition\, you’re welcome to bring your own food\, but no grills or ope
 n flames. You can also bring your own beer and wine but no glass\, and no 
 liquor or spirits.\nLocal breweries will be selling beer on site as well.\
 n\n**Accessibility**\nThere is a place to drop off patrons near the front 
 gate. The event is an open field with a slight slope. There are no sidewal
 ks\, but the grass is not thick and wheelchairs are able to roll through t
 he grass.
URL;VALUE=URI:https://www.meetup.com/raleigh-triangle-activities/events/31
 4179950/
STATUS:CONFIRMED
CREATED:20260408T134405Z
LAST-MODIFIED:20260408T134405Z
CLASS:PUBLIC
END:VEVENT
